        "content": [
          "Reflexive verbs often pair with PREPOSITIONS:",
          "",
          "sich gewöhnen AN + AKK = get used to",
          "Ich gewöhne mich an das Wetter.",
          "(I'm getting used to the weather)",
          "",
          "sich freuen AUF + AKK = look forward to",
          "Ich freue mich auf das Wochenende.",
          "(I'm looking forward to the weekend)",
          "",
          "sich freuen ÜBER + AKK = be happy about",
          "Ich freue mich über das Geschenk.",
          "(I'm happy about the gift)",
          "",
          "MORE COMMON REFLEXIVE + PREPOSITION:",
          "sich ärgern über + AKK (be annoyed about)",
          "sich erinnern an + AKK (remember)",
          "sich kümmern um + AKK (take care of)",
          "",
          "The preposition changes the meaning!",
          "Must memorize verb + preposition + case."
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 51"
      }
    ]
