        "content": [
          "Making comparisons in German:",
          "",
          "COMPARATIVE (more):",
          "Add -er to the adjective (+ endings)",
          "klein → kleiner",
          "groß → größer (note umlaut!)",
          "",
          "COMPARING WITH 'ALS' (than):",
          "Der Zug ist schneller als das Auto.",
          "(The train is faster than the car)",
          "",
          "Berlin ist größer als München.",
          "(Berlin is bigger than Munich)",
          "",
          "Er ist älter als ich. (He's older than me)"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 48"
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "SUPERLATIVE (most):",
          "Add -STE + adjective endings",
          "der kleinste Tisch (the smallest table)",
          "die schönste Stadt (the most beautiful city)",
          "",
          "COMMON IRREGULAR FORMS:",
          "gut → besser → beste (good/better/best)",
          "viel → mehr → meiste (much/more/most)",
          "gern → lieber → liebste (gladly/prefer/favorite)",
          "",
          "UMLAUT CHANGES:",
          "alt → älter → älteste (old/older/oldest)",
          "groß → größer → größte (big/bigger/biggest)",
          "jung → jünger → jüngste (young/younger/youngest)",
          "",
          "ADVERBIAL SUPERLATIVES:",
          "am meisten (at the most)",
          "am spätesten (at the latest)"
        ]
      }
    ]
