    "title": "LESSON 39: MODAL PARTICLES",
    "header_color": "cyan",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "Modal particles add TONE and NUANCE:",
          "",
          "bloß/nur - just, only (with urgency)",
          "Was machst du bloß? (What ARE you doing?)",
          "Wo ist er bloß? (Where ON EARTH is he?)",
          "",
          "doch - contradiction, encouragement",
          "Das ist doch klar! (That's obvious!)",
          "Komm doch mit! (Do come along!)",
          "",
          "mal - softens requests",
          "Komm mal her! (Come here! - friendly)",
          "Schau mal! (Look! - casual)",
          "",
          "ja - confirms shared knowledge",
          "Das ist ja interessant! (That IS interesting!)",
          "Du weißt ja... (As you know...)"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 39"
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "MORE MODAL PARTICLES:",
          "",
          "eigentlich - actually, by the way",
          "Was machst du eigentlich? (What are you up to?)",
          "",
          "überhaupt - at all, anyway",
          "Verstehst du das überhaupt? (Do you understand",
          "this at all?)",
          "",
          "halt/eben - just the way it is",
          "Das ist halt so. (That's just how it is)",
          "So ist es eben. (That's just the way it is)",
          "",
          "These particles don't translate directly.",
          "Listen for them in German speech.",
          "They add natural flow and emphasis!"
        ]
      }
    ]
